The paper proposes a novel framework that improves the performance and speed of signal recovery by jointly training a generator and the optimization process for reconstruction via meta-learning. This framework combines compressed sensing with neural network generators and explores training the measurements with different objectives. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions the use of Generative Adversarial Nets (GANs), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a novel way of improving GANs using gradient information from the discriminator, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing).
